<asp:Content ID="Content2" ContentPlaceHolderID="ContentPlaceHolder1" Runat="Server">
    <table align="center" class="style15" 
        style="padding: 3px; margin: 3px; border-style: solid;">
        <tr>
            <td class="style20">
                Frequently Asked Questions For Sales Interview:</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td class="style24">
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    1) How do you keep up to date on your target market?</span><span style="font-size:13.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    Even if the target market of their last job is totally different from the one 
                    they’re interviewing for, this will show their ability to find and keep up with 
                    relevant trade publications and blogs.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    2) Explain something to me.</span><span style="font-size:13.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;
mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    While this technically isn’t a question, it’s important to assess whether the 
                    candidate can effectively walk someone through a concept or process.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    3) In your last position, how much time did you spend cultivating customer 
                    relationships versus hunting for new clients, and why?</span><span style="font-size:13.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    Certain companies and roles call for people who are better at farming or 
                    hunting, but look out for a person who performs one of these tasks to the 
                    exclusion of the other. Both are vital to sales.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    4) What are your favorite questions to ask prospects?</span><span style="font-size:
13.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    Good salespeople spend more time asking questions than pitching. Look out for 
                    open-ended questions that will help a rep thoroughly understand a prospect’s 
                    needs.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    5) What’s your approach to handling customer objections?</span><span style="font-size:13.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    Preparing to deal with objections -- instead of winging it -- is critical. 
                    Listen for evidence of a process.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    6) What role does social media play in your selling process?</span><span style="font-size:13.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    Social selling is becoming more important in all industries. If the candidate 
                    has not used social channels to research prospects or look for leads in the 
                    past, make sure they have a willingness to learn.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    7) What role does content play in your selling process?</span><span style="font-size:
13.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    Again, it’s not necessarily a deal breaker if the salesperson doesn’t actively 
                    share and engage with content on their social media accounts, but they should be 
                    receptive to doing so.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    8) How do you research prospects before a call or meeting? What information do 
                    you look for?</span><span style="font-size:13.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    Neglecting to use LinkedIn to research clients is not a viable option in today’s 
                    sales environment. Ensure that candidates are searching for personal 
                    commonalities in addition to professional information so they can tailor 
                    communication as much as possible. Looking into company trigger events would be 
                    the cherry on top.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    9) If you were hired for this position, what would you do in your first month?</span><span style="font-size:13.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    The answer to this question doesn’t have to blow you away. However, the 
                    candidate should have some sort of action plan to get started. No matter how 
                    much training you provide, it’s still smart to hire a self-starter when you can.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    10) What do you think our company/sales organization could do better?</span><span style="font-size:13.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    This sales interview question serves two purposes: It shows how much research 
                    the candidate did before meeting with you, and it demonstrates their creative 
                    thinking and entrepreneurial capabilities.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    11) How does [your company name] bring value to the customer?</span><span style="font-size:13.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    This is another question that shows how much research your candidate has done on 
                    the company. If they can&#39;t even slightly articulate the benefits of your 
                    product/service, it might mean you need to move on.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    12) What&#39;s something you&#39;ve taught yourself lately?</span><span style="font-size:13.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    You want to hire salespeople who are hungry for new skills and better selling 
                    strategies. This question helps you find those people.<o:p></o:p></p>
                <p class="MsoNormal">
                    <span class="style23" 
                        style="mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family: Helvetica; color: #33475B; letter-spacing: .1pt">
                    13) What are three important qualifying questions you ask every prospect?</span><span style="font-size:13.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#33475B;letter-spacing:.1pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
                <p class="style21" 
                    style="mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">
                    This answer will be different for every candidate based on what they&#39;re selling 
                    and whom they&#39;re selling to. But their answer will allow you to gauge how they 
                    qualify prospects. It also gives you a further sense of their sales training and 
                    instincts.<o:p></o:p></p>
            </td>
        </tr>
